# Tailwind CSS v4 Styling Guide

## CSS Import Syntax

```css
/* Use v4 syntax in globals.css */
@import "tailwindcss";
@import "tw-animate-css";

/* CSS variables for theming */
:root {
  --primary: 0.205 0 0;
  --secondary: 0.97 0 0;
  --background: 1 0 0;
  --foreground: 0.145 0 0;
}
```

## Color System

- Use CSS variables for consistent theming
- Prefer semantic color names over arbitrary values
- Use oklch color space for better color representation

## Component Styling

```tsx
// Use semantic class combinations
<div className="bg-background text-foreground border border-border rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm">
  <h2 className="text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">
    Component Title
  </h2>
  <p className="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">Component description</p>
</div>
```

## Responsive Design

- Mobile-first approach
- Use responsive prefixes: `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`
- Test on multiple screen sizes

## Animation Classes

```tsx
// Use custom animation classes
<motion.div
  className="animate-fade-in animate-slide-up"
  initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 20 }}
  animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
  transition={{ duration: 0.5 }}
>
  Animated content
</motion.div>
```

## Dark Mode Support

```css
/* Use CSS variables for dark mode */
@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
  :root {
    --background: 0.145 0 0;
    --foreground: 0.985 0 0;
  }
}
```

## Utility Classes

- Prefer utility classes over custom CSS
- Use `@apply` directive for complex component styles
- Keep component styles in `@layer components`

